HEADWORD: Bob-cherry
<hw>Bob"-cher`ry</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A play among
children, in which a cherry, hung so as to bob against the mouth, is to
be caught with the teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

